messages.message:
So I tried updating (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/64948) the type hints for the grpc client to specify that the return type is the same as `func`, and I found soo many type errors. Most of them seem simple to fix. However, there seem to be less clear.

```instabase/jobs/job_handler.py:576: error: Incompatible types (expression has type "float", TypedDict item "start_timestamp" has type "datetime")
instabase/jobs/job_handler.py:577: error: Incompatible types (expression has type "float", TypedDict item "finish_timestamp" has type "datetime")
instabase/jobs/job_handler.py:670: error: Incompatible types (expression has type "float", TypedDict item "start_timestamp" has type "datetime")

instabase/flow_handler/flow_handler.py:875: error: Incompatible types in assignment (expression has type "List[<nothing>]", target has type "str")
instabase/flow_handler/flow_handler.py:876: error: Incompatible types in assignment (expression has type "bool", target has type "str")
instabase/flow_handler/flow_handler.py:880: error: Incompatible types in assignment (expression has type "List[str]", target has type "str")
instabase/flow_handler/flow_handler.py:885: error: Incompatible types in assignment (expression has type "bool", target has type "str")

shared-utils/py-utils/aihub-utils/src/py/instabase/build_utils/document.py:376: error: Argument "date_added" to "Document" has incompatible type "int"; expected "str"
shared-utils/py-utils/aihub-utils/src/py/instabase/build_utils/document.py:386: error: Argument "class_updated_at" to "Document" has incompatible type "int"; expected "str"```
cc @Elan Sharony on the aihub-utils errors since Andy is OOO
Let me take a look into this tomorrow. The job_handler errors looks straightforward. Need to check a little deeper for the flow_handler errors
